  "response_text": "The commercial begins inside a dim, elegant restaurant with warm amber lighting, lace-covered round tables, red flowers, wine glasses, plates, and other diners in the background. At the main table, a blonde woman in a pale, soft-looking dress sits beside a dark-haired man in a gray suit and patterned tie. He holds an open menu or wine list, studying it while a bald waiter in a black tuxedo and bow tie stands just behind them. The woman looks toward the waiter and then toward her companion, appearing uncertain at first. The man gestures with the menu as if ordering, and the waiter leans in attentively. The table is set formally, with empty wine glasses, folded napkins, and a small vase of red carnations at the center.\n\nThe waiter reacts with a broad, amused smile, while the seated couple look at each other. The man smiles sheepishly, still holding the wine list, and the woman’s expression shifts from puzzled to entertained. A different diner, a man in glasses and a suit, is then shown at another table or nearby seat. He adjusts his eyeglasses with one hand and peers downward as if reading, then looks up and speaks, also seeming to struggle with the wine name. The bald waiter smiles even more, turns his head aside, and laughs openly, his face relaxed and amused rather than stern.\n\nBack at the main table, the couple and waiter continue smiling over the order. Another couple at a nearby table appears, a dark-haired woman in a patterned blouse and a man in a tan suit. They sit close together at a table with a basket or tray of fruit and glasses, laughing and leaning toward each other, as if sharing in the joke. The scene returns to the main couple, now visibly more relaxed; the woman laughs, and the man looks down at the menu with a pleased, slightly self-conscious smile while the waiter stands close behind them.\n\nThe product is then shown prominently: a green, curved bottle held by a hand, beaded with condensation. Its cream-colored label reads Fazi-Battaglia, with Verdicchio visible beneath, and the neck has a red seal and pale wrapping. The bottle is tilted over an empty stemmed wine glass. A pale white wine pours in a steady stream, splashing and swirling inside the glass, forming bubbles and foam as the level rises.\n\nThe suited man is shown again, now smiling warmly with the waiter behind him holding the bottle nearby. He speaks animatedly and turns toward the blonde woman, who laughs beside him. The view widens to the restaurant table: the bottle stands on the table near the red flowers, and another waiter in a tuxedo stands to the right holding a white cloth or napkin. Several people around the table and in the background smile and applaud. The blonde woman leans affectionately toward the seated man, touching or holding his arm as the bald waiter laughs behind them. The atmosphere is festive and social, with diners and staff gathered around the couple.\n\nThe restaurant scene fades behind a large product display. The green Fazi-Battaglia bottle stands centered on a softly lit surface, with its label and red neck seal visible. Large white lettering appears across the screen reading “Fazi-Battaglia,” with smaller text to the right reading “imported from Italy.” The final image holds on the bottle against a dark background, emphasizing the brand name and Italian origin.",
